WeRateDogs Blog Post¶

WeRateDogs is a Twitter account that rates people's dogs with a humorous comment about the dog. These ratings almost always have a denominator of 10. The numerators, though? Almost always greater than 10. 11/10, 12/10, 13/10, etc. Why? Because "they're good dogs Brent." WeRateDogs has over 4 million followers and has received international media coverage.

Using 3 datasets that were manually, programmatically downloaded using Requests and Twitter API, I created a tidy master dataset for the analysis and visualization. I retrieved Retweet_count and Favorite_count for the Twitter using the Twitter API.

Insights and Visualization¶

Combining the 4 stages of Dogs to one column called dog_stage, I analyzed the values counts of each the stages that produced a bar graph below:

From the bar graph you see the distribution of the dog stages:

  • Pupper having the highest distribution of more than 250
  • Floofer having the lowest distribution of less than 50

Using the sort_values function on favourite counts produced the following insight:

  • tweet 823 of Tweet_ID : 744234799360020481 has the highest favorite count of 143730
  • The merged dataset has more that 2094 rows of data
